# GPA & Scholarship Eligibility Calculator Backend

This backend project provides the API for a GPA & Scholarship Eligibility Calculator designed for ADA University students. It calculates a student's GPA based on letter grades and course credits and determines scholarship eligibility based on defined criteria.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Tech Stack](#tech-stack)
- [Setup Instructions](#setup-instructions)
- [API Endpoints](#api-endpoints)
- [Testing](#testing)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Features

- **GPA Calculation:** Computes weighted GPA from letter grades and corresponding course credits.
- **Scholarship Eligibility:** Determines if the calculated GPA meets the threshold for scholarship eligibility.
- **Error Handling:** Provides meaningful error messages for invalid inputs.
- **Open Source:** Built for collaborative development and future enhancements.

## Tech Stack

- **Backend Framework:** Node.js with Express
- **Database:** Optional (configured for MongoDB connection)
- **Testing:** Jest and Supertest

